.scss file


styles.scss

/*-- scss:functions --*/
@function colorToRGB ($color) {
  @return "rgb(" + red($color) + ", " + green($color) + ", " + blue($color)+ ")";
}

/*-- scss:defaults --*/
$h2-font-size:          1.6rem !default;
$headings-font-weight:  500 !default;

/*-- scss:rules --*/
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  text-shadow: -1px -1px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, .3);
}


you can define sass variables and write css in scss files


Learn more: https://quarto.org/docs/output-formats/html-themes-more.html

Sass and brand.yml
The colors defined in the brand.yml palette are available as Sass with the format $brand-COLOR_NAME.


styles.scss

/*-- scss:rules --*/

h1 {
  color: $brand-blue;
}

h2 {
  color: $brand-green
}
